{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2c683428-03ac-4e2e-8e6f-a2ebb3ebad8b","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events** API in your `MauiProgram.cs` (or anywhere you configure the app builder):\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs when the activity is pausing\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs when the activity is no longer visible\n        }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // runs when the app enters the background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\nMake sure you have:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n```\n\nThis maps directly to the native events without needing custom platform code or renderers.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9eb7a290-0a28-4292-bae1-8f86dbbae798","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI - specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development that I can answer directly without needing to search files or run commands.","outputTokens":304,"requestId":"A857:2A55B4:666018:7665F3:69FBE2B2"},"id":"4b7c09e6-3276-4a7f-8f3f-03c003eb7e7d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:54:17.372Z","parentId":"6c76703d-de16-4473-8e12-e2c57c3bced1"}
